President Trump met with President Bukele of El Salvador to discuss their cooperation agreement, which aims to address issues such as MS-13 and forced migration. Both presidents expressed their appreciation for each other and their commitment to strengthening the relationship between their countries. Secretary McAleenan also praised President Bukele's efforts in ending forced migration and highlighted the successful cooperation agreements with other Central American countries. President Trump commended Mexico for its efforts in controlling the border and praised the Mexican President for working with the US. However, he criticized the Democrats in Congress for not addressing issues such as loopholes in immigration laws and asylum policies. President Trump also mentioned the ongoing impeachment inquiry against him, referring to it as a "hoax" and a continuation of the witch hunt.